g.text: PAGER CACHE ARCHITECTURE: THE DATA LIFECYCLE

div.p: Temporal Locality: The Pager keeps slot_a in memory because Milestone 3 (VDBE) is likely to request it again in the next cycle.
Dirty Bit Strategy: When vdbe_layer modifies a value, Dirty is flipped to 1 in slot_b. The Protector (M6) ensures this isn't written to the Warehouse until the WAL (Write Ahead Log) is finalized.
Memory Alignment: Data at pager_system.page_cache.slot_a.Data is aligned to 4KB boundaries to ensure the OS Kernel can perform zero-copy transfers.
